refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 boolmkdir
 stringdirectory
 intpermissions0777
 boolrecursive&false;
 resourcenullcontext&null;



 Attempts to create the directory specified by directory.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 &return.success;




  If the directory to be created already exists, that is considered an error
  and &false; will still be returned.  Use is_dir or
  file_exists to check if the directory already exists
  before trying to create it.

&reftitle.errors;
Emits an E_WARNING level error if the directory already exists.
Emits an E_WARNING level error if the relevant permissions prevent creating the directory.

  &reftitle.examples;



    mkdir example


<?php
mkdir("/path/to/my/dir", 0700);
?>







    mkdir using the recursive parameter


<?php
// Desired directory structure
$structure = './depth1/depth2/depth3/';

// To create the nested structure, the $recursive parameter 
// to mkdir() must be specified.

if (!mkdir($structure, 0777, true)) {
    die('Failed to create directories...');
}

// ...
?>
